{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#9125: \"Missing required prop\" warning after mounting component with union as props",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:45.074045+00:00",
  "text": "\"Missing required prop\" warning after mounting component with union as props\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.3\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#__DEV__\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nOpen console; observe warning.\n\n### What is expected?\n\nNo warning.\r\n\r\nalternatively, one of:\r\n- a proper error which says you can't make the props a union\r\n- a way to suppress this warning for a specific component (eg an attribute on `<script>`)\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n![image](https://github.com/vuejs/core/assets/14184826/723efb72-956b-4dd1-b079-8eda53662523)\r\n\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nSystem:\r\n    OS: Linux 6.5 Manjaro Linux\r\n    CPU: (12) x64 AMD Ryzen 5 3600 6-Core Processor\r\n    Memory: 19.29 GB / 31.23 GB\r\n    Container: Yes\r\n    Shell: 3.6.1 - /usr/bin/fish\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 20.5.1 - /usr/bin/node\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.19 - /usr/bin/yarn\r\n    npm: 9.8.1 - /usr/bin/npm\r\n  npmPackages:\r\n    vue: ^3.3.4 => 3.3.4\n```\n\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: script-setup"
  ],
